    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> |(<hi rend="print"> Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Tyndall</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I return the Siren with very many thanks.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> The plants, ill-luck to them, are not sensitive to aerial vibrations. I am ashamed at my blunder, &amp; very much more so at having vainly given you great trouble. I have, however, been glad to see the famed Siren.</p>
<p>My dear Tyndall | Yours truly obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11774.xml">letter from John Tyndall, 5 December 1878</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Tyndall had lent CD a siren for his experiments with sensitive plants; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11771.xml">letter to John Tyndall, 4 December [1878]</ref> and n. 3, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11774.xml">letter from John Tyndall, 5 December 1878</ref>.</note>
        </div>  
      
